  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/5086",
  "title": "Top-level HierarchicalMenu facet counts incorrect when combined with RefinementList",
  "body": "## 🐛 Bug description\r\n\r\nWhen you have both:\r\n- A RefinementList with a value selected (\"Brand: Samsung\")\r\n- A HierarchicalMenu with at least a second level selected (\"Category: Audio > Headphones\")\r\n\r\nThe facet counts on the root level items in the HierarchicalMenu are wrong.\r\n\r\n## 🔍 Bug reproduction\r\n\r\nThis is easy to reproduce in the samples:\r\nhttps://react-instantsearch.netlify.app/examples/e-commerce/search/\r\n\r\n1. Select **Brand: Samsung** and **Category: Audio**. All is ok so far: \r\n\r\n![2022-08-16 19_07_59-E-commerce demo _ Algolia](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/46369335/184842870-abde17bf-e250-4415-bc86-1c5740054b20.png)\r\n\r\n2. Now select the second level category **\"Audio > Headphones\"**\r\n\r\nThe facet counts on the top-level categories are all incorrect - they have reverted to their original, unfiltered value (before the brand was selected). Some previously hidden categories have even re-appeared, and selecting them immediately returns no results and gives a very jarring UX.\r\n\r\nConfusingly, the counts on the Audio category itself and its children are all correct.\r\n\r\n\r\n![2022-08-16 19_08_08-E-commerce demo _ Algolia](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/46369335/184843868-e366d5f3-1066-4e04-834e-a9f5c5e10891.png)\r\n\r\n",
